    <p>• The film is com­bined with a zinc coil and cop­per coil to form an elec­tro­chem­i­cal cell. When the film ab­sorbs mois­ture from sweat, elec­trons pass from the cop­per coil to the zinc coil, cre­at­ing an elec­tri­cal cur­rent.</p>
    <p>• In a demon­stra­tion, a gad­get con­tain­ing eight such cells is at­tached to a T-shirt, along with an LED light. The T-shirt is worn by a per­son who goes for a 10-minute run.</p>

